00:16:20.210 --> 00:16:21.850
and the amazing thing about, as you
listen to these lovely old tunes

00:16:21.850 --> 00:16:23.920
from the O'Farrel collection,
your immediate think--

00:16:23.920 --> 00:16:28.000
You immediately think, well, that
sounds like so and so, you know.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:29.990
That sounds just like
so-- that other tune.

00:16:29.990 --> 00:16:33.480
But it turns out the other tune
might have been written 200 years

00:16:33.480 --> 00:16:35.630
after this one from the
O'Farrel collection.

00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:36.930
&gt;&gt; Steve Winick: Right.

00:16:36.930 --> 00:16:40.340
&gt;&gt; Billy McComiskey: So that
stuff is really, really old.

00:16:40.340 --> 00:16:42.010
It might not be as old as the music

00:16:42.010 --> 00:16:43.660
from the Middle East,
