Tell me about Sean McGlynn.

00:24:59.210 --> 00:25:00.510
&gt;&gt; Billy McComiskey: Yeah.

00:25:00.510 --> 00:25:02.760
I will have trouble
talking about Sean.

00:25:02.760 --> 00:25:08.750 position:56%
Sean was a carpenter and-- by trade.

00:25:08.750 --> 00:25:12.540
And when he immigrated to Boston
and he met his wife there,

00:25:12.540 --> 00:25:16.360
Maura and he-- Well, he just
thought Maura had great style.

00:25:16.360 --> 00:25:19.000
Maura was also-- is
also from Galway.

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:26.310
Maura is still alive and we--
He had gone up to the Catskills.

00:25:26.310 --> 00:25:31.670
There was this one-- Again,
my godfather had a pub

00:25:31.670 --> 00:25:33.490
in the town of South Cairo.

00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:38.460
And my uncle was always coming
up with these little schemes

00:25:38.460 --> 00:25:41.930 position:56%
to get people to go so he could make
enough money to hang on with a bunch

00:25:41.930 --> 00:25:43.680
of kids, six or seven kids.

00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:47.580
Pat Murphy, crazy, completely.

00:25:47.580 --> 00:25:51.850
He was a great hurler but he
